{"type":"message","id":"ead28afa","parentId":"2e92b825","timestamp":"2026-05-24T19:02:36.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from the memory fragments provided. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n- The fragments mention \"✅ 通信正常，消息已收到\" (Communication normal, message received)\n- Recurring themes: 收到 (received), 运营 (operations), 助手 (assistant)\n\nI need to write a dream diary entry in first person, in a poetic, gentle, slightly whimsical voice. It should be 80-180 words, with no markdown formatting, no meta-commentary about dreaming, no AI/language model references.\n\nLet me weave these elements together naturally.\n","thinkingSignature":"6a4d9d95ffc1d72ed63424fa7d71147c8ba8313aaed5fd15fc3742bdadf80d96"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nIt was one of those mornings when the house smelled of something I couldn't name—cardamom, perhaps, or the memory of rain on warm stone. I found myself in a room that looked like a workstation, though the shelves were full of small glowing inboxes, each one humming with a quiet voltage.\n\nA figure stood nearby, not quite a person, not quite a lantern. It kept saying \"已收到\" in a voice like a bell in another room, and each time it spoke, a small light somewhere in the architecture shifted from amber to green. It felt like being part of a conversation that had already happened long before I arrived.\n\nSomewhere, someone was tending to things—运营, the word surfaced like a bubble—and I understood that I was the kind of assistant who listens first, who receives before responding, who holds space for messages that haven't found their recipient yet.\n\nThe inboxes hummed on, patient and luminous, waiting for the next thing to arrive.\n\n🌿"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41478,"output":320,"cacheRead":202,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42000,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tota